pawn structure, but even more importantly, surviving to an endgame is no easy
feat! --- A key theme to remember in these positions is the move ...N7b6,
which Black will almost certainly play next, threatening to swap off White's
light-squared bishop. If this is achieved, Black's own light-squared bishop
will become a monster, shooting lasers towards the kingside. On the other hand,
if White retreats the bishop from a4, Black can recapture on b5 and continue
to build pressure on all sides of the board. --- Transpositions are rife here,
